This paper deals with image forensics, which involves detecting different types of image editing operations carried out on an image. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper proposes a deep learning-based method, which involves training a deep siamese neural network to classify image patches as similarly or differently processed. This involves image manipulation detection, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The paper also deals with detecting forgeries in images, which falls under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. The proposed method involves training a neural network to learn features that can discriminate between different image editing operations, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image processing and analysis, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
